Using the function open() doesn't close a file after use - and it is good practice to do so!
While you can use close(), it is somewhat cleaner to use a "with open()" statement 

# is for comments
""" is for docstrings (but can also be for long string comments)
docstrings are used when defining functions, etc.
They are different!
https://www.pythonforbeginners.com/comments/when-to-use-comments-vs-docstrings-in-python

Unicode can be used to convert characters to integers using the ord() function
You can do the reverse (convert ints to strs) using the chr() function 

Regular expressions can be used to define search patterns!
https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_regex.asp